for thyroid disorder and then become pregnant,

532
00:24:47.910 --> 00:24:49.980
as soon as they become pregnant,

533
00:24:49.980 --> 00:24:51.960
you should increase their dose

534
00:24:51.960 --> 00:24:55.710
by 25 to 50% because that's what they'll need.

535
00:24:55.710 --> 00:24:59.730
You don't want to use anti-thyroid meds for women

536
00:24:59.730 --> 00:25:02.370
with gestational hyperthyroidism.

537
00:25:02.370 --> 00:25:04.533
You would use a beta blocker instead.

538
00:25:05.490 --> 00:25:09.570
And again, for Graves, PTU in the first semester,

539
00:25:09.570 --> 00:25:11.340
otherwise metamizol for the second

540
00:25:11.340 --> 00:25:13.020
and third trimester.

541
00:25:13.020 --> 00:25:15.380
Postpartum thyroiditis is very common up to five to 10%.

542
00:25:15.380 --> 00:25:17.550
So that's a good one to remember.

543
00:25:17.550 --> 00:25:19.980
Most of these patients will convert back

544
00:25:19.980 --> 00:25:23.070
to a euthyroid state, but you should monitor them.

545
00:25:23.070 --> 00:25:25.470
If they need supplementation,

546
00:25:25.470 --> 00:25:27.120
go ahead and initiate supplementation

547
00:25:27.120 --> 00:25:28.680
for six months to a year

548
00:25:28.680 --> 00:25:31.080
and then you can continue to monitor them

549
00:25:31.080 --> 00:25:32.970
and wean them as necessary.

550
00:25:32.970 --> 00:25:36.780
Again, don't use any radioactive iodine in a pregnant woman

551
00:25:36.780 --> 00:25:41.400
because that will also destroy the fetuses thyroid.

552
00:25:41.400 --> 00:25:42.990
So here are your recommendations.

553
00:25:42.990 --> 00:25:44.460
Your review slide

554
00:25:44.460 --> 00:25:46.410
to go back to and take a look.

555
00:25:46.410 --> 00:25:49.650
This is a 58 person, year old person with hypertension

556
00:25:49.650 --> 00:25:50.940
and an elevated calcium

557
00:25:50.940 --> 00:25:53.370
that comes back just on routine lab work.

558
00:25:53.370 --> 00:25:55.563
He denies any complaints on his exam.

559
00:25:57.309 --> 00:25:58.380
Is otherwise unremarkable.

560
00:25:58.380 --> 00:26:01.350
Additional labs are significant for an elevated calcium,

561
00:26:01.350 --> 00:26:04.680
an elevated PTH, low phosphate levels,

562
00:26:04.680 --> 00:26:07.770
and you suspect that he has hyperparathyroidism.

563
00:26:07.770 --> 00:26:12.330
All the following are common except bone pain,

564
00:26:12.330 --> 00:26:17.013
increased appetite, depression, or renal stones.

565
00:26:22.440 --> 00:26:25.050
That teeny tiny little gland, good.

566
00:26:25.050 --> 00:26:27.270
So I think everybody remembers this.

567
00:26:27.270 --> 00:26:30.930
The bone stones, abdominal moans and psychic groans.

568
00:26:30.930 --> 00:26:33.243
Everybody remember that from way back when.

569
00:26:34.410 --> 00:26:37.020
They're still the number one symptoms

570
00:26:37.020 --> 00:26:38.670
for a hyper parathyroid state.

571
00:26:38.670 --> 00:26:41.700
So hyperparathyroidism much, much,

572
00:26:41.700 --> 00:26:44.790
much more common than hypoparathyroidism.

573
00:26:44.790 --> 00:26:48.390
So the more common question on any board exam,

574
00:26:48.390 --> 00:26:50.550
considering that the parathyroid gland

575
00:26:50.550 --> 00:26:52.860
will be a hyperparathyroid state

576
00:26:52.860 --> 00:26:54.660
treatment is to take it out.

577
00:26:54.660 --> 00:26:56.430
There's no medication to treat this.

578
00:26:56.430 --> 00:26:57.423
You take it out.

579
00:26:58.692 --> 00:26:59.820
There are primary and secondary reasons

580
00:26:59.820 --> 00:27:01.290
just to consider this.

581
00:27:01.290 --> 00:27:04.563
Again, the adenomas are always, always the culprit.

582
00:27:05.568 --> 00:27:07.349
They're everywhere.

583
00:27:07.349 --> 00:27:08.820
There's on the AFP website, there's a webinar

584
00:27:08.820 --> 00:27:11.280
that I did a few years ago about adenomas that you,

585
00:27:11.280 --> 00:27:13.110
if you want to go back and take

586
00:27:13.110 --> 00:27:15.993
a deeper dive into adenomas, that is there for you,

587
00:27:16.950 --> 00:27:18.240
but you're gonna take it out.

588
00:27:18.240 --> 00:27:21.520
Secondary causes are most commonly chronic kidney disease

589
00:27:22.548 --> 00:27:26.100
and low vitamin D states, which will trigger the parathyroid

590
00:27:26.100 --> 00:27:27.993
to become more hyperactive.

591
00:27:30.090 --> 00:27:33.030
Quick little snapshot at the different elements

592
00:27:33.030 --> 00:27:37.590
that can contribute to hypercalcemia, which are numerous.

593
00:27:37.590 --> 00:27:40.323
You can have the parathyroid hormone related proteins,

594
00:27:41.171 --> 00:27:42.121
that could do it.

595
00:27:42.121 --> 00:27:43.200
Vitamin D intoxication.

596
00:27:43.200 --> 00:27:47.670
If you give someone 50,000 units of vitamin D for weeks,

597
00:27:47.670 --> 00:27:49.743
which we did to one of our patients once,

598
00:27:51.503 --> 00:27:55.140
they become toxic and hypercalcemic.

599
00:27:55.140 --> 00:27:58.170
Granuloma, just disease sarcoid, TB can do it.

600
00:27:58.170 --> 00:27:59.250
Hodgkin's lymphoma

601
00:27:59.250 --> 00:28:01.320
and then a variety of different malignancies.

602
00:28:01.320 --> 00:28:05.370
Those will be mainly the PTH related protein ones

603
00:28:05.370 --> 00:28:07.710
and the head and neck squamous cell carcinomas.

604
00:28:07.710 --> 00:28:10.113
So those are the the two big ones to remember.

605
00:28:11.430 --> 00:28:13.260
And then there are medications.

606
00:28:13.260 --> 00:28:14.580
Why thiazide?

607
00:28:14.580 --> 00:28:17.580
This is the fourth time thiazides have come up during

608
00:28:17.580 --> 00:28:19.110
the last 24 hours.

609
00:28:19.110 --> 00:28:21.090
Again, the thiazides reabsorb calcium,

610
00:28:21.090 --> 00:28:23.820
so they're gonna increase your calcium levels.

611
00:28:23.820 --> 00:28:25.810
So that is good for

612
00:28:27.450 --> 00:28:29.280
kidney stones,

613
00:28:29.280 --> 00:28:30.703
bad for.

614
00:28:30.703 --> 00:28:31.536
<v Speaker>Count</v>

615
00:28:31.536 --> 00:28:32.369
<v ->Count, that's right.</v>

616
00:28:33.583 --> 00:28:34.770
Other endocrine disorders to think about.

617
00:28:34.770 --> 00:28:35.790
Adrenal insufficiency,

618
00:28:35.790 --> 00:28:37.770
we're gonna touch on that in a moment.

619
00:28:37.770 --> 00:28:39.420
Familial issues.

620
00:28:39.420 --> 00:28:44.010
And then anytime you have high bone turnover, paget disease,

621
00:28:44.010 --> 00:28:47.572
rhabdo, etcetera, you can see hypercalcemia.

622
00:28:47.572 --> 00:28:49.410
Hypoparathyroidism, ultra rare,

623
00:28:49.410 --> 00:28:51.330
probably won't be on the test.

624
00:28:51.330 --> 00:28:53.910
Happens 900 patients per year

625
00:28:53.910 --> 00:28:56.730
and the only treatment for it is supplementation.

626
00:28:56.730 --> 00:28:57.723
Supplementation.

627
00:28:59.100 --> 00:29:00.690
Getting towards the end here.

628
00:29:00.690 --> 00:29:03.240
33-year-old patient presents

629
00:29:03.240 --> 00:29:06.630
with irregular menses in galactorrhea for three months.

630
00:29:06.630 --> 00:29:10.680
The remainder of her history and physical are unremarkable.

631
00:29:10.680 --> 00:29:12.630
Your lab studies are within normal limits

632
00:29:12.630 --> 00:29:15.450
except for a prolactin that's 310.

633
00:29:15.450 --> 00:29:17.540
What do you do next?

634
00:29:17.540 --> 00:29:19.800
Do you do a dexamethasone suppression test?

635
00:29:19.800 --> 00:29:21.603
PET scan, an MRI or a CT?

636
00:29:27.600 --> 00:29:28.433
Good.

637
00:29:28.433 --> 00:29:32.790
You are worried about a brain tumor

638
00:29:32.790 --> 00:29:34.470
that could be secreting prolactin.

639
00:29:34.470 --> 00:29:35.370
Perfect.

640
00:29:35.370 --> 00:29:37.290
So this is a prolactinoma.

641
00:29:37.290 --> 00:29:38.123
Remember the rule.

642
00:29:38.123 --> 00:29:39.030
Two hundreds.

643
00:29:39.030 --> 00:29:41.010
If you have prolactin greater than 200,

644
00:29:41.010 --> 00:29:43.140
this is almost always a prolactinoma.

645
00:29:43.140 --> 00:29:44.640
Consider pregnancy tests.

646
00:29:44.640 --> 00:29:46.080
Also consider what else could be

647
00:29:46.080 --> 00:29:47.700
happening in the thyroid gland.

648
00:29:47.700 --> 00:29:50.220
MRI will always be more definitive.

649
00:29:50.220 --> 00:29:54.450
CT can be helpful in certain certain situations,

650
00:29:54.450 --> 00:29:57.300
but think about what is globally happening in the pituitary

651
00:29:57.300 --> 00:29:58.470
because lots of things can happen.

652
00:29:58.470 --> 00:30:00.390
You can have prolactin that's secreted.

653
00:30:00.390 --> 00:30:02.910
You can have growth hormones that are secreted.

654
00:30:02.910 --> 00:30:04.590
You can have Cushing's disease

655
00:30:04.590 --> 00:30:06.780
where corticotropin are secreted

656
00:30:06.780 --> 00:30:10.473
and you can have hyper thyroidism if TSH is affected.

657
00:30:11.640 --> 00:30:13.170
Again, MRI number one.

658
00:30:13.170 --> 00:30:17.310
If you're worried about a Craniopharyngioma or meningoma,

659
00:30:17.310 --> 00:30:19.950
CT can sometimes be better for that.

660
00:30:19.950 --> 00:30:22.980
Again, differential for a cellar mass.

661
00:30:22.980 --> 00:30:27.780
Benign pituitary adenomas will always be number one.

662
00:30:27.780 --> 00:30:29.460
There are some malignant ones to come back

663
00:30:29.460 --> 00:30:31.470
and look to you a little bit later.

664
00:30:31.470 --> 00:30:34.080
Craniopharyngioma is seen on CT.

665
00:30:34.080 --> 00:30:38.403
This is the crankcase oil, are generally benign tumors.

666
00:30:39.780 --> 00:30:43.830
So very briefly, a couple slides on Cushing's and Addison's,

667
00:30:43.830 --> 00:30:45.630
then we'll wrap it up here.

668
00:30:45.630 --> 00:30:46.980
Cushing's syndrome.

669
00:30:46.980 --> 00:30:50.940
You think about getting crushed, crushed by cortisol.

670
00:30:50.940 --> 00:30:52.560
If you have increased cortisol state,

671
00:30:52.560 --> 00:30:54.300
it contributes to all of these things.

672
00:30:54.300 --> 00:30:57.930
Hypertension, even increased WBCs,

673
00:30:57.930 --> 00:31:00.480
plethora, etcetera.

674
00:31:00.480 --> 00:31:03.780
The treatment for Cushings is to try

675
00:31:03.780 --> 00:31:07.020
to identify the source, reducing the steroid use.

676
00:31:07.020 --> 00:31:09.420
Sometimes you may need to consider radiation.

677
00:31:09.420 --> 00:31:12.480
So if it's an adenoma that's causing it,

678
00:31:12.480 --> 00:31:14.043
you will need to take it out.

679
00:31:15.570 --> 00:31:18.360
Just note, the higher prevalence of patients with diabetes,

680
00:31:18.360 --> 00:31:21.180
obesity, hypertension, and osteoporosis.

681
00:31:21.180 --> 00:31:22.950
Those are the four buckets

682
00:31:22.950 --> 00:31:24.990
that you most commonly see Cushings.

683
00:31:24.990 --> 00:31:28.922
And it happens in a younger population, 25 to 40.

684
00:31:28.922 --> 00:31:30.090
How do you diagnose it?

685
00:31:30.090 --> 00:31:30.923
There are a number of things

686
00:31:30.923 --> 00:31:32.987
to diagnose it, but the number of one

687
00:31:32.987 --> 00:31:37.203
methodology is the dexamethasone suppression test.

688
00:31:38.234 --> 00:31:39.990
So that's a not an uncommon question.

689
00:31:39.990 --> 00:31:42.420
Might want to go back and just refresh later on.

690
00:31:42.420 --> 00:31:45.450
How do you do a dexamethasone suppression test?

691
00:31:45.450 --> 00:31:48.000
And Addison's is the opposite of Cushing's disease.

692
00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:50.790
So Addison's, you have to add more cortisol.

693
00:31:50.790 --> 00:31:52.980
So it's a decreased cortisol state.

694
00:31:52.980 --> 00:31:57.240
It's a decreased aldosterone state that leads most commonly

695
00:31:57.240 --> 00:31:58.800
to a primary disorder.

696
00:31:58.800 --> 00:32:01.710
But you can have secondary reasons for Addison.

697
00:32:01.710 --> 00:32:03.690
So that would be happening at the level

698
00:32:03.690 --> 00:32:07.803
of the pituitary glands, and where a CTH is inadequate.

699
00:32:09.418 --> 00:32:10.251
The clinical presentation,

700
00:32:10.251 --> 00:32:12.150
is sort of the opposite of of Cushing's disease.

701
00:32:12.150 --> 00:32:14.670
So you have low blood pressure instead of high,

702
00:32:14.670 --> 00:32:17.370
you have weight loss, you have muscle cramps,

703
00:32:17.370 --> 00:32:19.680
salt cravings, etcetera.

704
00:32:19.680 --> 00:32:22.623
You have your electrolyte imbalances accordingly.

705
00:32:23.649 --> 00:32:25.800
So diagnosis includes looking for those things.

706
00:32:25.800 --> 00:32:29.160
You might consider doing a CTH STEM test.

707
00:32:29.160 --> 00:32:32.610
You would eventually get a CT scan of the adrenals

708
00:32:32.610 --> 00:32:34.650
to take a closer look.

709
00:32:34.650 --> 00:32:37.320
Treatment will be to replace the cortisol

710
00:32:37.320 --> 00:32:39.630
and to consider replacing the aldosterone.

711
00:32:39.630 --> 00:32:41.850
So here are your summary pearls to go back

712
00:32:41.850 --> 00:32:43.830
and reflect on later,

713
